Cinema company Ster-Kinekor has announced that it will start reopening its cinemas around the country on August 28. Cinemas in South Africa have been closed since March 27 and the company said the reopening will be conducted in a phased approach to ensure that employees have been trained on the Covid-19 health and safety measures and all the PPE required are ready when reopening. Ster-Kinekor will start by reopening 32 cinemas followed by the remaining 21  on September 18. Various safety measures will be put in place to ensure cinemas are  safe for customers, including: A list of other regulations  the company has implemented can be viewedÂ here.